### Mixins (Options API)

Mixins are a way to distribute reusable functionality in the Options API:

```js
// mixins/logger.js
export const loggerMixin = {
  created() {
    console.log(`${this.$options.name} created`)
  },
  methods: {
    log(msg) {
      console.log(`[Log] ${msg}`)
    }
  }
}
```

Usage:

```vue
<script>
import { loggerMixin } from './mixins/logger'
export default {
  mixins: [loggerMixin],
  created() {
    this.log('Component mounted')
  }
}
</script>
```

### Mixin Merging

- **Data**: Deep merged, component data takes precedence
- **Lifecycle hooks**: Both called (mixin hooks run before component hooks)
- **Methods/Computed**: Component takes precedence if same key exists

### Custom Directives

Custom directives allow low-level DOM access:

```js
// directives/focus.js
export default {
  mounted(el) {
    el.focus()
  }
}
```

Global registration:

```js
app.directive('focus', { mounted: (el) => el.focus() })
```

Local registration:

```vue
<script>
export default {
  directives: {
    focus: { mounted: (el) => el.focus() }
  }
}
</script>

<template>
  <input v-focus />
</template>
```

### Directive Hooks

| Hook | Description |
|---|---|
| `created` | Called before element's attributes applied |
| `mounted` | Element is mounted to the DOM |
| `beforeUpdate` | Called before element updates |
| `updated` | Element's children have updated |
| `beforeUnmount` | Called before element is unmounted |
| `unmounted` | Element has been unmounted |

### Passing Values to Directives

```vue
<div v-highlight="{ color: 'yellow', duration: 300 }"></div>

<script>
app.directive('highlight', {
  mounted(el, binding) {
    el.style.backgroundColor = binding.value.color
  }
})
</script>
```

codeExample:
// v-tooltip directive
app.directive('tooltip', {
  mounted(el, binding) {
    el.style.position = 'relative'
    const tooltip = document.createElement('span')
    tooltip.textContent = binding.value
    tooltip.className = 'tooltip-text'
    tooltip.style.cssText = 'display:none;position:absolute;bottom:100%;left:0;background:#333;color:#fff;padding:4px 8px;border-radius:4px;font-size:12px;white-space:nowrap'
    el.appendChild(tooltip)

    el.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => { tooltip.style.display = 'block' })
    el.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => { tooltip.style.display = 'none' })
  },
  updated(el, binding) {
    const tooltip = el.querySelector('.tooltip-text')
    if (tooltip) tooltip.textContent = binding.value
  },
  unmounted(el) {
    const tooltip = el.querySelector('.tooltip-text')
    if (tooltip) tooltip.remove()
  }
})

// Usage: <button v-tooltip="'Save changes'">Save</button>
